<ns763:section xmlns:ns763="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.solms.training.courses.ProjectManagement.ProjectManagement">

  <ns764:title xmlns:ns764="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Project Management</ns764:title>
  <ns765:para xmlns:ns765="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    The project management course aims to provide project managers an understanding of managing software
    development projects through all its phases including  initiation, planning, execution, controlling and closing.
    It covers modern software development processes including model-driven development (MDD),
    eXtreme Programming (XP) and RUP as well as the underlying architectural and design processes.
    The course covers estimation, planning, risk management, status assessment and reporting. Additionally
    candidates will receive a conceptual understanding of widely used technologies, like J2EE, SOA, .Net, XML, Web Services, ..., 
    their benefits and risks as well as typical application domains for them.
  </ns765:para>
  
  <ns766:section xmlns:ns766="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.solms.training.courses.ProjectManagement.targetAudience">
    <ns767:title xmlns:ns767="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">For whom is the course meant?</ns767:title>
    <ns768:para xmlns:ns768="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      This course targets current and aspiring project managers who would like to be able to effectively
      manage projects in the context of modern, iterative and model-driven software development
      methodologies.
    </ns768:para>
  </ns766:section>

  <ns769:section xmlns:ns769="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.solms.training.courses.ProjectManagement.outcomes">
    <ns770:title xmlns:ns770="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Outcomes</ns770:title>
    <ns771:para xmlns:ns771="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      After successful completion of the course candidates should be able to
      <ns772:itemizedlist xmlns:ns772="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        <ns773:listitem xmlns:ns773="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns774:para xmlns:ns774="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          the role players in a software development project and their responsibilities,
        </ns774:para></ns773:listitem>
        <ns775:listitem xmlns:ns775="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns776:para xmlns:ns776="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          core project management concepts and project variables,
        </ns776:para></ns775:listitem>
          <ns777:listitem xmlns:ns777="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns778:para xmlns:ns778="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
            common causes of project failure as well as best practices for project management,
          </ns778:para></ns777:listitem>
        <ns779:listitem xmlns:ns779="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns780:para xmlns:ns780="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          manage the full project life cycle through initiation, planning, execution, controlling and closing, 
        </ns780:para></ns779:listitem>
        <ns781:listitem xmlns:ns781="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns782:para xmlns:ns782="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          be able to understand and manage project scope,
        </ns782:para></ns781:listitem>
        <ns783:listitem xmlns:ns783="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns784:para xmlns:ns784="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          be able to identify and quantify project risks, formulate risk-response strategies and perform effective
          risk management,
        </ns784:para></ns783:listitem>
        <ns785:listitem xmlns:ns785="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns786:para xmlns:ns786="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          introduce and manage effective estimation processes including standard and improved Wide Band Delphi (the latter
          provides not only estimates on the time/cost, but also on the perceived risk), and Use Case Points estimation (the
          modern equivalent of function point analysis),
        </ns786:para></ns785:listitem>
        <ns787:listitem xmlns:ns787="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns788:para xmlns:ns788="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          understand and manage the moderns software development processes like RUP and Extreme Programming,
          and understand their benefits and shortcomings,
        </ns788:para></ns787:listitem>
        <ns789:listitem xmlns:ns789="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns790:para xmlns:ns790="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          understand that architecture and design are orthogonal and have a solid understanding of modern 
          quality-attribute driven architecture,
        </ns790:para></ns789:listitem>
        <ns791:listitem xmlns:ns791="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns792:para xmlns:ns792="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          an understanding of URDAD, the Use-Case, Responsibility Driven Analysis and Design process, its benefits and an
          understanding of how it provides an integrated business process / system design process.
        </ns792:para></ns791:listitem>
        <ns793:listitem xmlns:ns793="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns794:para xmlns:ns794="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          the benefits of MDA (Model Driven Architecture), how it facilitates that design outlives technologies, and how URDAD
          can be used within the context of MDA,
        </ns794:para></ns793:listitem>
        <ns795:listitem xmlns:ns795="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns796:para xmlns:ns796="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          have a high-level understanding of modern implementation technologies including enterprise architecture (J2EE, 
          Services Oriented Architectures (SOAs), and .Net), integration technologies (XML, web services, CORBA, RMI, Remoting),
          development languages (Java, C#, ...) and persistence technologies (relational, object and XML databases),
        </ns796:para></ns795:listitem>
        <ns797:listitem xmlns:ns797="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns798:para xmlns:ns798="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          an understanding of the Capability Maturity Model (CMM) and how it aims to assist organizations too grow towards
          higher levels of maturity and hence be able to successfully pull through larger and more complex projects.
        </ns798:para></ns797:listitem>
        <ns799:listitem xmlns:ns799="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns800:para xmlns:ns800="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        </ns800:para></ns799:listitem>
      </ns772:itemizedlist>
    </ns771:para>
  </ns769:section>

